*Ciaran McAuley plays Monday Bar Cruise* 

Monday Bar is a gig I‚Äôve chased from way back in my Walsh&McAuley days! so I am absolutely delighted to announce this one

Monday Bar Sweden

So last night I made my debut in Germany at Techno Club in Frankfurt. I was invited over to celebrate trance legend Talla 2xlc 39years in the scene! 

I had such a great night in Technoclub with everyone, this iconic venue has been going strong now 35 years, so it was pleasure to not only see the place but to play. 

After my set a guy came to tell me he has been going to the trance gigs there for over 15 years and has never heard music that made him feel so good.

Debut after debut with sweaty hugs and handshakes I‚Äôm truly touching people from every corner of the globe with my sound, receiving nothing but great energy and smiles. 

I‚Äôve already been invited back, I look forward to see you all again ‚ù§Ô∏è

Congrats and thank you Talla 2XLC

data.message:
I Care And Im There

A few weeks back I teamed up with Tamhi in N.Ireland, taking their brand and voice to the stage at Shorefest. 
With this collaboration I would like to raise awareness and help others to understand the issue's around Mental Health.

Between 2000 and 2017 a total of 4,476 deaths were listed as suicide in Northern Ireland, and while the numbers across the UK fell in that time, in Northern Ireland they soared from 185 in 2000 to 305 in 2017.

I've been in some scary dark places mentally and spent time learning why and how to overcome these times. Talking seems like such an easy step but I know how hard it is but please do trust me, get it out, be open about it, there's nothing to be ashamed of. I regularly speak to people privately on my social media platforms to help him through their darkness, I am here and I do care.

Never fade away little one...

Never Fade Away (Benthe) is a track I wrote for Benthe Beerepoot a 5 year old girl who suffered a severe progressive rare disease. She lived in a loving home surrounded by a trance family, music always made her smile. Unfortunately Benthe passed away on Saturday so much earlier then we ever could have imagined but in great loving care of her parents Jeroen and Merlijn and her big brother Tijmen Beerepoot. I never met Benthe in person but with the regular updates and videos from her nurse the loss truly hit me. My thoughts have been with them, I wish them all the love and light in the world. 

Thanks to Ruben & Armin for sharing this with the world

Take me back...

One of my ‚Äústand out‚Äù tracks from my sets all summer Julie Thompson - Shine is finally seeing its release this Monday on Grotesque Music. It got its first spin on the main stage @ Luminosity Events back in June, it was my intro that set the tone for my highly spoke of set.

data.message:
How bad do you want to succeed? 

Being back home in Belfast I always try fit in my Cavehill fix. This morning I wake for a nice casual walk of it and find out I‚Äôve no car at hand to get me there, it was cold, raining and foggy but without a second thought I grabbed my coat and run up on the hope of catching or even seeing a sunrise. I‚Äôm not here looking a pat on the back but on my way up it crosses my mind how this corresponds to life itself. So many ask how or why I am so ‚Äúsuccessful‚Äù, I‚Äôm flattered by the comments of course but it‚Äôs no secret, I actually post daily my routines and steps, I even encourage others to move forward and better themselves. 

Again guys, play close attention to your daily rituals, become obsessed with improvement and challenge yourself each day.

The next two weeks I join these trance legends on their sold out Common Ground Tour. This Friday we take to the biggest venue in N.Ireland, The Telegraph Building, Belfast. It‚Äôs not very often I get the opportunity to play my much loved progressive sounds so I‚Äôm really looking forward to this.

See you all soon!
